parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description:
The client token that is used to ensure the idempotence of the request.

You can use the client to generate the value, but you must make sure that it is unique among different requests. The token can contain only ASCII characters.

>  If you do not specify this parameter, **ClientToken** is set to the value of **RequestId**. The value of **RequestId** in each API request may be different.

parameters.name: QosDescription
parameters.description:
The description of the QoS policy.

The description must be 0 to 256 characters in length and cannot start with `http://` or `https://`.

parameters.name: QosName
parameters.description:
The name of the QoS policy.

The name must be 0 to 128 characters in length and cannot start with `http://` or `https://`.

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description:
The region ID of the QoS policy.

You can call the [DescribeRegions](~~36063~~) operation to query the most recent region list.

parameters.name: ResourceGroupId
parameters.description: The ID of the resource group.

parameters.name: Tags
parameters.description: The tag to add to the resource.
